"    Light micrograph in fibrillary glomerulonephritis shows diffuse expansion of the mesangium by amorphous, acellular material (arrows). Electron microscopy and Congo red staining are necessary to distinguish this light microscopic appearance from amyloidosis or light chain deposition disease.",
